<subSubSection id="748FA8E0A7E3234969C0F2CDE0B3F702" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="978BC4404BCE089CAEFC29AE4B65C800" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="BC09987F52907DD464EDDA9F7FD6052A" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
4.1-4.5 mm long (mean = 4.26 mm; n = 5); 2.2-2.28
<normalizedToken id="3E2FA3BA5B9445CD59C3BEF81974731D" originalValue="Ã">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. This species is distinguished by the small size; elytral disc convex, without a transverse saddle-like depression; declivital posterolateral margins costate, never carinate; and boundary between elytral disc and declivity smoothly rounded.
</paragraph>
